# Static site (agent)

- This is HTML5 static website
- Markup should be minimalistic, use pure tags like <b>, <ul>, <p>, <h1>, etc. when possible
- Images live under `images/`
- CSS is `main.css`
- CSS should use styles (.x), not ids (#x)
- PDFs live under `dl/`
- Website should be adaptive, min supported width is 320px
- Every page should have breadcrumbs in a style 'Home /' or 'Home / Topics /'. Current page title is NOT added in the breadcrumbs - it's already there in <h1> below.
- Every page has contents menu with top-level links. Some top-level links are aggregated under 'Sessions' category, but they should still be considered as top-level. The current page’s entry in Contents must be plain bold text (`<b>…</b>`), never a link to the same URL. On a deeper page (e.g. a single topic), parent sections stay normal links; only the leaf that matches the current page is non-link bold.

When working on content (not on global markup by explicit request):
- Minimal additions and changes to CSS are allowed, for huge ones request confirmation